HEADWORD: Chest founder
<hw>Chest" foun`der</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>A
rheumatic affection of the muscles of the breast and fore legs of a
horse, affecting motion and respiration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

